<body>
    <h1>Get Compatible Products</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"1cefb049c8e5"><strong>Component type:</strong> Actio=
n</p>
<p local-id=3D"e7aca2289408"><strong>Category:</strong> Billing &amp; Produ=
cts</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"13661c968583" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-Overview">Overvie=
w</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9d25a7efb0e9">The <strong>Get Compatible Products</strong> a=
ction checks which products from a given list are compatible with a specifi=
c reservation. It splits the provided products into two groups: those that =
can be ordered for the reservation and those that cannot. This is useful fo=
r filtering product options before presenting them to a guest or before aut=
omatically adding products to a reservation =E2=80=94 for example, ensuring=
 that only valid upsell products are offered during a pre-arrival workflow.=
</p>
<p local-id=3D"fe9085a4fffa">The component has two output ports: <strong>Co=
mpatible Products</strong> and <strong>Incompatible Products</strong>. Each=
 port provides the list of product IDs and product names for its respective=
 group. If all products are compatible, only the <strong>Compatible Product=
s</strong> port fires; if all are incompatible, only the <strong>Incompatib=
le Products</strong> port fires.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9c455847-238c-43f4-bc85-15765eefff3b">
<h2 local-id=3D"711297291f44" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-InputFields">Inpu=
t Fields</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"115054a6-fa57-408c-9ebf-5c3=
662bd15d5" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c0cbdc7f-e8af-42f6-8b3b-4d30bbae91b2">
<th data-local-id=3D"9c094486-1f6d-48c4-8f6e-6a91347b74c9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"c29e6640f14d">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"46408477-cdbc-4617-bac7-8b4e65b6e0eb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"af7d3385c8d3">Required</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"07c00ce1-b8fd-4033-884e-8f756e8036ba" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"99c0430070e7">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"901e6074-ba75-45c4-8b59-14c2a95f922d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"9bdf9a76c120">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"358a22cb-25d3-4708-97c9-57afb2d88584">
<td data-local-id=3D"619a720f-2c4b-4e78-8ded-883edd4927af" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d600a83a7ceb"><strong>Reservation ID</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c983031e-f645-4e41-8588-b2f0c1b39f3a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"761b456325e0"><strong>Required</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4577c45d-9d88-47b2-bb96-3c6188bdb322" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0d8e43c88af9">Text (GUID)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b5c81897-27c5-43e6-aca0-c07fb7d4ef3b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c2a41f13d542">The unique identifier of the reservation to ch=
eck product compatibility for. The reservation must exist and belong to the=
 current property. Typically populated dynamically from a previous step in =
the workflow (e.g., a trigger that provides a reservation ID).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"892b516c-72a4-406e-9afa-004f8a64d233">
<td data-local-id=3D"24170359-ce1e-4c3e-8916-4a560853f6a9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c7195527455e"><strong>Products</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6e202c93-ddfd-4c87-ba08-292c5ab1537c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"31560854e3fd"><strong>Optional</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f0cc563f-6390-4e8e-9429-6d50762ff388" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6fa5c8019df0">Multi-select</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6c80047b-dc89-4846-ac36-13f0f371b5a9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"61e4b15fbbc2">The products to check for compatibility. The d=
ropdown is populated dynamically with the products configured in your prope=
rty. You can select one or more products. If no products are selected, both=
 output ports will have empty results.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"9cdfbfb7fc43"><strong>Note:</strong> The <strong>Products</s=
trong> field is populated from the list of all products available in your p=
roperty. You can select multiple products to check at once.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"545558df-1654-473c-8159-dd76e703a49e">
<h2 local-id=3D"1bd86bfbe4c4" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-OutputFields">Out=
put Fields</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2cb103cc4910">The component has two output ports. Each port =
fires only when it has at least one product in its group.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"811acc5be91a" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-CompatibleProduct=
sport">Compatible Products port</h3>
<p local-id=3D"56bb990c2692">Products that are valid and can be ordered for=
 the reservation's service.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"24955222-9831-4802-bba0-46f=
1ba509843" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a771d92b-d396-4c59-965d-4970379b3b77">
<th data-local-id=3D"ebdf49de-9981-4327-a727-d28fef811d11" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"08b5db4139da">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"e4892713-e9e5-4737-ac2b-5476de433ff3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"8e7c451354f2">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"0e557aaa-73ab-4777-ad5b-bc7e2ad4cb3c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ba2e6720525b">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4f24da3d-719c-4ce1-8719-24022eafa9b3">
<td data-local-id=3D"582f55d5-6331-4485-9ec9-907997db7477" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8eee191b0542"><strong>Compatible Product IDs</strong></p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"b1f4797e-4959-4737-af42-b5ef944d5478" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6be0d1308186">Array of Text (GUIDs)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"18c34a1a-9296-447b-bba1-c3f7b1ca8998" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cbc3ccea259b">The unique identifiers of the products that ar=
e compatible with the reservation.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6dea3e7a-22a1-42a0-b6e8-c8acc97f0be6">
<td data-local-id=3D"4cb67a45-7397-415b-aa88-06a330f79477" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e699bc6425a4"><strong>Compatible Product Names</strong></p><=
/td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b6b2e4cd-44aa-4bff-85ca-419da690c65b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"09a8ba0d40c2">Array of Text</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9c0eb637-4234-4aea-85a5-ca5bd0eb1ab3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d5cfac7fee7d">The localized display names of the compatible =
products.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"1cf682b75bb9" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-IncompatibleProdu=
ctsport">Incompatible Products port</h3>
<p local-id=3D"a841c924557e">Products that cannot be ordered for the reserv=
ation due to one or more compatibility rules.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d8682e49-6046-4cf3-8580-32b=
66841875e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"0d3afe79-ede1-4fb1-b3cd-70c789fc79eb">
<th data-local-id=3D"e027863f-b200-4eb1-b9bc-a996d2c5d3fd" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"479ec895cc48">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"2fbf8bc2-0047-491c-bcbd-b8ef4fd9b677" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a1036e758a62">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"d63d14b7-d2a1-4d26-b1cd-9899a9ce0df9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"f4e9bff97aeb">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"918018aa-322f-4aa6-a834-b09963d77e64">
<td data-local-id=3D"1c5621e6-fc87-4a3e-8f2e-656f917accc8" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"af1b41164304"><strong>Incompatible Product IDs</strong></p><=
/td>
<td data-local-id=3D"128007bc-76ab-4caa-a6a8-cff556ac2491" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fc0c19c38fc8">Array of Text (GUIDs)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a4e93682-5673-4558-8734-4a1737759535" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e66db4e733d9">The unique identifiers of the products that ar=
e not compatible with the reservation.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"32b35d6c-53be-46db-9730-8f6650916a02">
<td data-local-id=3D"0c0d4b5d-f495-40c8-b19d-6ad5fe002b8e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8cf866a78de9"><strong>Incompatible Product Names</strong></p=
></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"59116495-baf6-4bfc-ba63-82b546690317" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a4a5ab1ca3d0">Array of Text</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ccd6886b-62a6-42f9-9c8d-2e8d8b7be662" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d7d0c6ebe265">The localized display names of the incompatibl=
e products.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"6df85d2c-4158-4452-be79-3a2e8eadd37d">
<h2 local-id=3D"f183f32faa4c" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-CompatibilityRule=
s">Compatibility Rules</h2>
<p local-id=3D"1629a17e8e3a">A product is considered <strong>compatible</st=
rong> with a reservation when <em>all</em> of the following conditions are =
met:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"05819ba5-c8c5-4ebe-8622-bcda67d60474">
<li local-id=3D"b9622e02-04f7-42ae-8d7a-fcd1aaca80d6">
<p local-id=3D"294b75c2409b"><strong>Same service</strong> =E2=80=94 The pr=
oduct must belong to the same service (e.g., Accommodation) as the reservat=
ion.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5192be4f-adbf-465a-9dc5-0902210cc22c">
<p local-id=3D"762785de4111"><strong>Not a default product</strong> =E2=80=
=94 The product must not be marked as a default product in Mews. Default pr=
oducts are automatically included with the service and cannot be added sepa=
rately.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"dce4a108-fcef-42f2-b942-dc33d078d7cc">
<p local-id=3D"a3ef67f82609"><strong>Offered to employees</strong> =E2=80=
=94 The product must have the "Offer to Employee" option enabled, meaning i=
t is available for manual or automated ordering.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"2274a9ee4272">If a product fails <em>any</em> of these condi=
tions, it is classified as <strong>incompatible</strong>. Products that are=
 not found (e.g., a deleted or invalid product ID) are also classified as i=
ncompatible.</p>
<p local-id=3D"deb0333a47a0"><strong>Important:</strong> A product belongin=
g to a different service (e.g., a Spa product checked against an Accommodat=
ion reservation) will always be incompatible, even if it meets all other cr=
iteria.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"38dd7112-fed3-4254-83f0-fcc78c2a194a">
<h2 local-id=3D"7ddbd701ad3c" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-HowItWorks">How I=
t Works</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"f8ecf42b-2d08-4db6-9d51-a80b152130cd">
<li local-id=3D"f4328834-0a52-4c5d-aa46-aa40e990ff51">
<p local-id=3D"4a64d2305417">The component receives a <strong>Reservation I=
D</strong> and an optional list of <strong>Products</strong> from the previ=
ous step in the workflow.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"970d2a30-3a48-4413-96b5-f3955b5a28ec">
<p local-id=3D"440313972ba4">It validates that the reservation exists and b=
elongs to the current property. If the reservation is not found, the compon=
ent returns an error.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a8a7ed1b-1884-4765-8020-d7f6b73fbb68">
<p local-id=3D"5d6be3602c8f">Each selected product is evaluated against the=
 compatibility rules (same service, not default, offered to employees).</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"bd36f5db-ac45-4c9d-8103-7b6ee9e8a4c6">
<p local-id=3D"6065483dc944">Products that pass all rules are sent to the <=
strong>Compatible Products</strong> output port with their IDs and localize=
d names.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cee55007-befd-4a2a-b2c4-b5aab2d07367">
<p local-id=3D"8fb35d2db3f3">Products that fail any rule are sent to the <s=
trong>Incompatible Products</strong> output port with their IDs and localiz=
ed names.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"525f48da-a58e-4403-8ee8-60d24d5b15ce">
<p local-id=3D"c6693bab9158">If a group is empty (e.g., all products are co=
mpatible), the corresponding output port does not fire.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"d76491c3-6fbb-4f2a-b88c-4b2ba0a63acc">
<h2 local-id=3D"bb9447c91845" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-ExampleUseCases">=
Example Use Cases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"2194b44d-992a-4a51-aecc-68f4e120238e">
<li local-id=3D"9d0aec6c-b95c-4c00-b135-912a5a5bae72">
<p local-id=3D"b70ce6c34b50"><strong>Pre-arrival upsell filtering</strong> =
=E2=80=94 Before sending a pre-arrival email with product offers, use this =
component to filter out incompatible products so the guest only sees releva=
nt options for their reservation.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0d937600-bd59-49aa-9ea3-394ae1d57914">
<p local-id=3D"8ffa799e0e77"><strong>Automated product ordering</strong> =
=E2=80=94 In a workflow that automatically adds products to a reservation (=
e.g., a welcome package), first validate that the products are compatible b=
efore attempting to order them.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4ab11399-8463-4a50-80e8-2e359e55b11d">
<p local-id=3D"a00edca36968"><strong>Product catalog validation</strong> =
=E2=80=94 When a property updates their product catalog, use this component=
 to verify which products remain compatible with existing reservations and =
flag any that need attention.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3d8b6a32-87a2-4048-9048-440b307b1f09">
<p local-id=3D"1117704e199e"><strong>Service-specific workflows</strong> =
=E2=80=94 When handling reservations across multiple services (e.g., Accomm=
odation and Spa), use this component to ensure that products are only added=
 to reservations for their matching service.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"5e54e7c7-7c43-494e-b006-294444df7369">
<h2 local-id=3D"ce633395897c" id=3D"GetCompatibleProducts-ErrorHandling">Er=
ror Handling</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
